{
  "stem": "9168.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "By that time I may have reported a, you know, outside of police headquarters.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I may have reported courtroom cases of murders maybe only half a dozen times before I went to Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So to me it really affected me very badly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The whole-- the whole period of time there affected me for my entire life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I never recovered from Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I never recovered from what I heard there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I came back with a different outlook on life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And you know, I could-- when I got to New York, for example, back to the big city with all the cocktail parties, and all the materialism and all-- I just-- for all of what I had heard, I really wanted to just turn around and go back to Europe, for some strange reason.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well I guess that having grown up in a small town, Woodstock, with one Jewish family, I did not know very much about bigotry, and especially on a scale of calculated genocide that the German hierarchy was involved in to exterminate all of the Jews of Europe-- not all of the Christians of Europe, as I have said.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I came back home with a whole new feeling, especially for Jews, and interest in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I got back to-- when my husband and I eventually got back to Detroit-- and I married an American MP officer over there-- I-- I had the feeling that I wanted to know more than I even knew then.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I can remember there was an ad in for-- about a videotape from the war trials at a Jewish synagogue.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't know what a Jewish synagogue was, other than that was the place of worship for the Jews as the church was for me.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
